value.0: You look about you, suspicious, but see nothing.

Moonstone shows an almost magical play of light as its characteristic feature. In many cultures it is considered a sacred and magical gemstone sometimes known as a "dream stone", When uncut, Moonstones look quite boring and make it difficult to discern their attractiveness: the mysterious play of light. It will only be brought out by the cutter's expertise and skills.
Volcanic produced stones of dark colors of gray, brown, and black. Treasured by Fire Giants and other fire worshiping creatures.  It is often touted as a charm against negative energies.

Pearls are an organic gem, created when an oyster covers a foreign object with beautiful layers. The quality of pearls is judged by the by the refraction of light by its layers and luster, the reflectivity and shine of the surface. Fine pearls do not have any flaws or spots and have an even, smooth texture. Other factors that affect value are the regularity of the shape, size, and color: rose tints are the most favored. They are thought to keep children safe and keep newlywed women from crying.
Jet is fossilized gem quality coal. Often burned as incense in Dwarven temples.  Dwarves consider it to be good protection against ill fortune.

The jewelry of the sea; corals need not necessarily be red, although the name "Coral" denotes a pinkish-red color. Nature creates Coral in a wide range of shades and hues from red and white and blue to brown and black. Most coveted are the red shades, ranging from palest petal pink via salmon to deep velvety red.
A opening in the ground to a dungeon -- usually were you put someone to forget them.
